post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is only true in the case of people whose drug use either causes them to become dangerous or interferes with their lives. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Foreign countries' dealers might find it convenient to resupply in a nearby country where drugs have been legalized, thus boosting the phenomenon of international drug trafficking, expensive to track down and halt."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Optimal treatment of addiction sometimes means [needing to taper off](https://www.therecoveryvillage.com/heroin-addiction/heroin-taper/) a drug, however, under prohibition quitting "cold turkey" is the only legal option. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalising drug use would not significantly increase the consumption of drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Although not all people are affected in this way, the risk for psychosis is higher [when regularly consuming cannabis with a high concentration of THC.](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2801827/)'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "It's always going to be cheaper to produce a product legally. Legal producers don't have to worry about having their stuff stolen by police and can do all their transactions in the legal market which is much more efficient and cheaper."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would significantly decrease social stigma and discrimination against users who have been incarcerated for employment and education opportunities.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs have a long history of responsible use within their historical context.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, as of 2018 there are roughly [235,000](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2018.html) inmates behind bars for drug-related crimes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The banning of alcohol [significantly increased the ability of organized crime to make money](http://prohibition.themobmuseum.org/the-history/the-rise-of-organized-crime/the-mob-during-prohibition/). That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The same applies to already legal alcohol. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many poor people use drugs as a temporary escape from poverty [\\(Scottish Drugs Forum, p. 12\\)](http://www.dldocs.stir.ac.uk/documents/drugpovertylitrev.pdf). Criminalization of this behavior does not help them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is preferable that if people are going to take drugs, the profit of the industry go to the government to use to provide important services rather than to gangs or drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}
